  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing human rights integration into the humanitarian response in Northeast Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to strengthen existing OHCHR assistance to increase the protection of at risk populations through enhanced protection responses, monitoring, sustained advocacy and risk mitigation. The protection of the rights of individuals is at the core of humanitarian response. The humanitarian community faces the challenge of  protecting victims of Boko Haram insurgency as well as those affected by the counter-insurgency operations by national security agencies. There is therefore an urgent need to enhance OHCHR engagement and strengthen human rights capacity support to the humanitarian response more specifically on prevention and response to violations of IHL/IHRL. The envisaged support will enhance coordinated monitoring and reporting, information management and analysis on violations and abuses, advisory support to the humanitarian leadership as well as timely human rights advocacy and response. Through this intervention, the capacity of key humanitarian actors and structures will be enhanced as well as their systematic engagement with UN human rights mechanisms. The proposed strengthening of OHCHR support to the humanitarian response aims at responding to the requests of the Nigerian Government in among others, its statement at the 31st session of the Human Rights Council as well as of the UN Country Team and humanitarian agencies. 
In sum, the project project covers costs for staff and key strategic activities including human rights advice, advocacy and capacity building. It aims at strengthening existing OHCHR engagement in Nigeria with regards to the insurgency in the Northeast, support human rights advocacy and capacity building: drafting reports, developing advocacy and communication tools, providing human rights advice, supporting community outreach and engagement at the strategic level as well as training and capacity building to enhance accountability and community resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
